@startuml PlanA-Sequence-Realtime-Presence
!theme plain
title PlanA — Sequence: Realtime Connection & Presence

skinparam shadowing false

actor "User A" as A
actor "User B" as B
participant "Web (A)" as WebA
participant "Web (B)" as WebB
participant "Caddy" as Caddy
participant "Realtime Hub\n(realtime/hub.go)" as Hub
participant "Client A\n(realtime/client.go)" as ClA
participant "Client B" as ClB
database "Redis\n(presence)" as Redis

A -> WebA : open project page
WebA -> Caddy : GET /api/ws (Upgrade)\nAuthorization: Bearer JWT
Caddy -> Hub : Upgrade()
Hub -> Hub : verify JWT, create Client A
Hub -> ClA : register
WebA -> Hub : subscribe { channel: "project:{pid}" }
Hub -> Redis : SADD presence:project:{pid} userA
Hub -> ClB : presence.join { userA } (if B already on channel)

B -> WebB : open same project
WebB -> Hub : WS upgrade & subscribe
Hub -> Redis : SADD presence:project:{pid} userB
Hub -> ClA : presence.join { userB }
Hub -> ClB : presence.snapshot { [userA, userB] }

== Live update during edit ==

A -> WebA : drag card to "In Progress"
WebA -> Caddy : PATCH /api/work-items/{id}
Caddy -> Hub : (handler runs, see other diagram)
Hub -> ClA : work_item.updated
Hub -> ClB : work_item.updated
WebA -> WebA : optimistic UI confirmed
WebB -> WebB : invalidate query cache, re-render

== Disconnect ==

A -> WebA : close tab
WebA -> Hub : WS close
Hub -> Redis : SREM presence:project:{pid} userA
Hub -> ClB : presence.leave { userA }

note over Hub
  Channels: project:{id}, org:{id}, epic:{id}.
  Frontend falls back to polling if WS is down.
end note

@enduml
